# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE exception list
#
# Add CVE IDs here (one per line) to suppress known/accepted vulnerabilities
# from Trivy SBOM scan results and SARIF uploads to GitHub Security.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Document the reason for each exception in a comment above the CVE ID
#   - Include an expiry date in the comment if the exception is time-bounded
#   - Review this file quarterly or whenever a new exception is added
#   - Remove entries when the underlying dependency is patched or removed
#
# Example:
#   # False positive — only reachable in test scope, not bundled in production
#   # Accepted until: 2026-06-01
#   CVE-2024-12345
